The article announces several appointments in the United States government. Craig J. Anderson is appointed as the United States Marshal for the District of Montana, replacing Rodney D. Ostermiller. Michael D. Black is appointed as the United States Marshal for the Southern District of Ohio, replacing Peter C. Tobin. Scott Winston Colom is appointed as the United States District Judge for the Northern District of Mississippi, replacing Michael P. Mills. Stephen K. Eberle is appointed as the United States Marshal for the Western District of Pennsylvania, replacing Michael D. Baughman. Justin L. Martinez is appointed as the United States Marshal for the District of Utah, replacing Matthew D. Harris. Nickolas Guertin is appointed as an Assistant Secretary of the Navy, replacing James F. Geurts. Finally, Roger F. Nyhus is appointed as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Barbados, as well as to the Federation of Saint Kitts and Nevis, Saint Lucia, Antigua and Barbuda, the Commonwealth of Dominica, Grenada, and Saint Vincent and the Grenadines.